01:10.026 --> 01:11.071
Hi!

01:42.928 --> 01:43.973
Um...

01:46.149 --> 01:47.281
Okay.

01:47.455 --> 01:49.500
- Another shot?
- Yeah, sure. Okay. Um...

01:53.374 --> 01:54.940
Hi. Hi, Reggie.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.203
<i>Laura, hi.</i>

01:56.377 --> 01:59.510
Hello. <i>Um, so nice to phone-meet you</i>

01:59.684 --> 02:01.164
<i>in this
incredibly embarrassing way.</i>

02:01.338 --> 02:04.385
Oh, you know, no-- no problem.
It's fine.

02:04.559 --> 02:07.518
<i>This is what I get
for picking a trendy place
with no sign out front, huh?</i>

02:09.303 --> 02:11.000
Yeah, why do they do that here? <i>I don't know.</i>

02:11.174 --> 02:13.133
<i>I've only been in the city
for a few months.</i>

02:13.307 --> 02:15.352
Me, too! No way! Yeah. <i>Oh, wow.</i>

02:15.526 --> 02:18.094
Well, um,
it's a very cool restaurant.

02:18.268 --> 02:20.618
Is it on Hudson? <i>Yes.</i>

02:20.792 --> 02:23.186
<i>Am I on Hudson?</i> I don't know.

02:23.360 --> 02:25.275
<i>I am not on Hudson. Shit.</i>

02:26.885 --> 02:28.887
<i>Uh, I am now
walking towards Hudson.</i>

02:29.061 --> 02:30.759
Okay. <i>I am so, so sorry.</i>

02:30.933 --> 02:32.326
<i>This is not
the first impression
I wanted to make</i>

02:32.500 --> 02:33.718
<i>on a college professor.</i>

02:33.892 --> 02:35.590
Oh, pfft. Associate Professor,

02:35.764 --> 02:37.679
and it's just
Film Studies, so...

02:37.853 --> 02:39.637
<i>Oh.</i>...you're safe.

02:39.811 --> 02:42.466
<i>Film Studies? That's...</i>
<i>...cool.</i>

02:42.640 --> 02:45.817
You say that,
but try teaching a class
on 20th-century slashers

02:45.991 --> 02:47.863
to a heap
of hungover 19-year-olds.

02:48.037 --> 02:49.865
<i>Slashers, huh?</i>

02:50.039 --> 02:52.128
<i>What's your favorite
scary movie?</i>

02:52.302 --> 02:54.174
Um, not that one.

02:56.001 --> 02:57.525
<i>So why slashers?</i>

02:57.699 --> 02:59.875
Well, I just, you know,
I think it's interesting.

03:00.049 --> 03:02.051
