37:06.180 --> 37:07.399
I got to ask...

37:08.748 --> 37:10.184
do you have alibis
for earlier tonight?

37:10.358 --> 37:12.621
I was at a party
with my friends.

37:12.795 --> 37:14.710
I was at my therapist's.

37:14.884 --> 37:17.670
I can give you his information.
You can call to check
if you want.

37:17.844 --> 37:19.585
And then I met Tara
at that party,

37:19.759 --> 37:21.326
where I tased someone.

37:22.414 --> 37:23.415
Unrelated.

37:25.155 --> 37:26.418
Was that before
or after this happened?

37:26.592 --> 37:27.984
<i>Murderer!</i>

37:28.158 --> 37:29.638
<i>What the fuck
is wrong with you, bitch?</i>

37:29.812 --> 37:32.032
<i>You got a problem with me?</i> Before.

37:32.206 --> 37:34.295
The point is,
we were with people all night.

37:34.469 --> 37:37.080
So, our roommate's dad

37:37.255 --> 37:39.387
just happened
to pull our case.

37:39.561 --> 37:41.389
That'd be a crazy coincidence, right?

37:41.563 --> 37:43.696
- Yeah.
- The detective who had the case,

37:43.870 --> 37:46.481
he offered it to me
because it involves Quinn.

37:46.655 --> 37:49.658
Um, but I can totally give it
back if you're uncomfortable.

37:49.832 --> 37:50.964
It's up to you.

37:54.968 --> 37:56.578
It's fine.

37:56.752 --> 37:59.364
So if the man who attacked you
did steal your license

37:59.538 --> 38:00.974
and plant it next to the body,

38:02.192 --> 38:04.369
it'd probably be somebody
close to you.

38:05.631 --> 38:07.415
How long have you known
your friends?

38:07.589 --> 38:08.982
Well, we moved here
with Mindy and Chad

38:09.156 --> 38:10.723
for summer semester,
like, six months ago.

38:10.897 --> 38:16.424
So, Quinn, um, Ethan, Anika--
all since then.

38:16.598 --> 38:20.385
I think I can vouch for Quinn,
so that's one less
we have to worry about.

38:20.559 --> 38:23.736
Do either of you have anyone
that might want to target you?

38:25.651 --> 38:27.305
Not anyone
who's still alive.

38:28.393 --> 38:29.742
Yikes.

38:29.916 --> 38:32.919
FBI's here,
claiming jurisdiction.

38:33.093 --> 38:34.137
Where are they?

38:40.274 --> 38:41.667
Can I help you?

38:44.713 --> 38:46.802
Special Agent Kirby Reed, FBI.

38:46.976 --> 38:48.587
I work out
of the Atlanta office.

38:48.761 --> 38:49.979
Oh. You lost?

38:51.894 --> 38:53.287
Your two vics
were residents of my city

38:53.461 --> 38:54.854
before they moved here
for college.

38:55.028 --> 38:56.986
I have been investigating
their online activity

38:57.160 --> 38:58.684
for the past few months.

39:00.773 --> 39:01.730
Wow.

39:01.904 --> 39:03.297
Why?

39:03.471 --> 39:06.039
I take a special interest
in Ghostface attacks.

39:06.213 --> 39:07.954
- Kirby?
- Hey, Sam.

39:09.303 --> 39:10.348
What?

39:11.044 --> 39:12.045
Tara.

39:12.828 --> 39:14.700
You're the FBI?Mm-hmm.

39:14.874 --> 39:16.963
- You guys know each other?
- Yeah.

39:17.137 --> 39:18.660
We went
to Woodsboro High together.

39:18.834 --> 39:20.749
She was a senior
when I was a freshman.

39:20.923 --> 39:23.012
We share a certain history, yeah.

39:23.186 --> 39:25.275
I'm not trying
to get into

39:25.450 --> 39:26.973
a jurisdictional
pissing contest here,

39:27.147 --> 39:28.540
I just want to help.

39:28.714 --> 39:31.934
I'll show you mine,
et cetera.

39:34.241 --> 39:35.285
Thank you.

39:36.548 --> 39:37.984
He left this mask
at the bodega.

39:38.158 --> 39:40.203
DNA traces of two individuals,

39:40.378 --> 39:42.989
Charlie Walker, Jill Roberts,
both deceased.

39:43.990 --> 39:46.601
The Ghostface killers of 2011.

39:47.863 --> 39:50.039
Charlie Walker gave me this.

39:50.213 --> 39:52.302
Like I said,
I take a special interest.

39:52.477 --> 39:55.001
Is this the mask he was wearing
when he attacked you?

39:55.958 --> 39:57.003
No.

39:57.177 --> 39:59.048
So he's leaving them
on purpose.

39:59.222 --> 40:00.659
Which means whoever's doing this

40:00.833 --> 40:02.878
is a student of the killers
who came before.

40:03.052 --> 40:04.097
Maybe he believes

40:04.271 --> 40:06.229
Sam is the latest
in a long line.

40:06.404 --> 40:09.755
Yeah, good luck with that.
We're getting out of town.

40:09.929 --> 40:12.322
I'm sorry,
that's not possible.

40:12.497 --> 40:15.151
You're both persons of interest
in a double homicide,

40:15.325 --> 40:17.197
so you're not allowed
to leave town. Sorry.

40:17.371 --> 40:19.591
- Are you serious?
- He's right.

40:19.765 --> 40:22.202
But if we work together--We're going.

40:27.468 --> 40:30.340
Samantha, do you have an alibi
for last night's murders?

40:30.515 --> 40:32.342
Tara, do you feel safe
around your sister?

40:32.517 --> 40:34.562
Tara! Tara!

40:34.736 --> 40:36.477
Gale Weathers, Channel 4.

40:37.522 --> 40:38.958
Do you ladies
think you're the reason

40:39.132 --> 40:41.003
the Ghostface killer
has come to the Big Apple?

40:44.877 --> 40:48.097
Nice try, sweetie,
but I've done this dance before.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.929
Stay away from us.

40:54.103 --> 40:55.627
Are you still mad at me?

40:55.801 --> 40:58.238
You said you wouldn't write
a book about what happened.

40:58.412 --> 40:59.979
And then you wrote a book
about what happened.

41:00.153 --> 41:01.241
Oh, come on.

41:01.415 --> 41:02.721
Somebody was gonna write
about it!

41:02.895 --> 41:04.244
It's what I do.

41:04.418 --> 41:05.898
I heard you couldn't sell
the movie rights.

41:06.072 --> 41:09.554
It's all about true-crime
limited series these days.

41:09.728 --> 41:11.599
After everything
we went through together.

41:12.470 --> 41:14.036
What would Dewey think?

41:15.864 --> 41:17.823
- That's a low blow.
- So was your book.

41:17.997 --> 41:20.956
You called me "unstable"
and a "born killer."

41:21.130 --> 41:24.307
- That's taken out of context.
- That's literally a quote.

41:24.482 --> 41:26.048
You don't think
what you wrote
has something to do

41:26.222 --> 41:28.007
with what's happening to us?

41:28.181 --> 41:30.096
Come on.

41:30.270 --> 41:32.054
Hey, I talked to Sidney.

41:35.144 --> 41:37.059
She's not coming here,
- is she?
- No.

41:37.233 --> 41:38.626
She sends her love,

41:38.800 --> 41:41.237
but she's taking Mark
and the kids someplace safe.

41:41.411 --> 41:43.588
She deserves
to have her happy ending.

41:45.546 --> 41:46.982
On that much, we agree.

41:48.331 --> 41:50.899
Hey, I want to catch this fucker
as much as you do!

41:51.073 --> 41:52.292
Maybe.

41:52.466 --> 41:53.728
Or maybe you're just afraid

41:53.902 --> 41:55.164
that without Ghostface
in your life,

41:55.338 --> 41:56.905
you're gonna fade away.

42:04.173 --> 42:06.175
<i>You fools! You're in danger!</i>

42:06.349 --> 42:09.135
<i>Can't you see?
They're after you!</i>

42:09.309 --> 42:11.354
<i>They're after all of us!
Our wives,</i>

42:11.529 --> 42:13.008
<i>our children, everyone!</i>

42:13.182 --> 42:16.490
<i>They're here already!
You're next!</i>

42:16.664 --> 42:21.626
<i>You're next! You're next!
You're next!</i>

42:21.800 --> 42:23.192
<i>You're next!</i>

42:31.679 --> 42:33.202
Who is it?

42:49.479 --> 42:53.222
You're a day early
for trick-or-treating, you know.

43:27.953 --> 43:31.304
<i>♪ Take a little walk
To the edge of town♪</i>

43:31.478 --> 43:33.349
<i>♪ And go across the tracks... ♪</i>

43:33.523 --> 43:36.004
Okay, nerds,
listen up!

43:36.178 --> 43:38.093
As terrifying
as this all is,

43:38.267 --> 43:40.530
I'm actually glad
I get a chance to redeem myself

43:40.705 --> 43:43.098
for not calling the killers
last time.

43:43.272 --> 43:45.884
- Yep.
- It's fine. Okay.

43:46.058 --> 43:49.496
The way I see it, someone is out
to make a sequel to the requel.

43:49.670 --> 43:51.324
Um, what's a requel?

43:51.498 --> 43:54.457
You're beautiful, sweetie.
Let's hold questions to the end.

43:54.632 --> 43:56.677
<i>Stab 1</i> took place
in Woodsboro.

43:56.851 --> 43:59.332
<i>Stab 2</i> took place in college.

43:59.506 --> 44:01.682
So we think that
the killer is trying
to copy the movies?

44:01.856 --> 44:03.292
That is one possibility.

44:03.466 --> 44:05.512
Heroes now in college:
Check.

44:05.686 --> 44:08.341
Suspicious new characters
brought in
to round out the suspect list

44:08.515 --> 44:11.605
and/or body count:
Check, check and check.
I don't like this.

44:11.779 --> 44:13.389
But it can't just be
about <i>Stab 2.</i>

44:13.563 --> 44:15.261
- Why not?
- It would make sense

44:15.435 --> 44:16.828
if this were just a sequel.

44:17.002 --> 44:18.307
But we're not in a sequel,

44:18.481 --> 44:20.658
because nobody
just makes sequels anymore.

44:23.138 --> 44:24.749
We're in a franchise!

44:24.923 --> 44:28.317
And there are certain rules
to a continuing franchise.

44:28.491 --> 44:30.450
- I had a feeling.
- Rule one:

44:30.624 --> 44:32.147
Everything is bigger
than last time.

44:32.321 --> 44:35.150
Bigger budget, bigger cast,
bigger body count.

44:35.324 --> 44:37.065
Longer chases, shoot-outs, beheadings.

44:37.239 --> 44:39.111
You got to top what came before
to keep people coming back.

44:39.285 --> 44:41.200
- Beheadings?
- Beheadings.

44:41.374 --> 44:44.725
Rule two:
Whatever happened last time,
expect the opposite.

44:44.899 --> 44:47.772
Franchises only survive
by subverting expectations.

44:47.946 --> 44:50.949
If the killers last time
were whiny snowflake film nerds

44:51.123 --> 44:52.994
with Letterboxd accounts
instead of personalities,

44:53.168 --> 44:55.780
you can bet
the opposite will be true here.

44:55.954 --> 44:59.261
And rule three:
No one is safe.

44:59.435 --> 45:02.177
Legacy characters?
Cannon fodder at this point.

45:02.351 --> 45:04.179
Usually brought back
only to be killed off

45:04.353 --> 45:06.399
in some cheap bid
for nostalgia.

45:06.573 --> 45:09.097
It's not looking too good
for Gale and Kirby.

45:09.271 --> 45:11.360
Oh, and that's
not even the worst part!

45:11.534 --> 45:13.493
This is the part where she
tells us the worst part.

45:13.667 --> 45:15.713
The worst part is

45:15.887 --> 45:20.282
franchises are just
continuing episodic installments
designed to boost an IP.

45:20.456 --> 45:22.589
Which means main characters

45:22.763 --> 45:24.852
are completely expendable now, too.

45:25.026 --> 45:28.290
Laurie Strode, Nancy Thompson,
Ellen Ripley,

45:28.464 --> 45:31.206
Sally Hardesty, Jigsaw,
Tony Stark, James Bond--

45:31.380 --> 45:33.034
I mean, even Luke Skywalker--

45:33.208 --> 45:35.776
all died so their franchises
could live on.

45:35.950 --> 45:38.170
That means it's not
just the friend group.

45:38.344 --> 45:41.086
Any of us could go
at any time,

45:41.956 --> 45:43.697
especially Sam and Tara.

45:45.699 --> 45:47.962
Wait, any of us?[Mindy] Yeah.

45:48.136 --> 45:50.748
Am I in the friend group?[Mindy] Yeah.

45:50.922 --> 45:53.359
Am I, like,
one of the targets?[Mindy] Mm-hmm.

45:54.577 --> 45:56.057
Am I gonna die a virgin?

45:57.885 --> 45:59.365
That was a weird overshare.

45:59.539 --> 46:01.715
But it brings us
to our current suspects:

46:02.281 --> 46:03.456
Ethan.

46:03.630 --> 46:05.066
The shy, dorky guy
who no one suspects

46:05.240 --> 46:06.938
because he's so shy and dorky.

46:07.112 --> 46:08.678
Why am I
on the suspect list?

46:08.853 --> 46:11.029
Because I'm randomly
Chad's roommate?

46:11.203 --> 46:12.944
Roommate lotteries
can be juked.

46:13.118 --> 46:15.163
You could have fixed it
to get next to us.

46:15.337 --> 46:16.425
Quinn.

46:16.599 --> 46:17.905
The slutty roommate.

46:18.079 --> 46:19.733
A horror movie...
...classic.

46:19.907 --> 46:22.562
"Sex positive,"
but... thank you?

46:22.736 --> 46:25.695
Mm-hmm. Um, how did you come
to live with Sam and Tara?

46:25.870 --> 46:28.002
I answered their ad online.

46:28.176 --> 46:29.395
Okay, say no more.

46:29.569 --> 46:31.484
You've already implicated
yourself enough.

46:31.658 --> 46:33.225
It was an anonymous ad, Mindy.

46:33.399 --> 46:35.488
And you know we vetted her.
Plus her dad is a cop.

46:35.662 --> 46:37.577
And that makes it more likely
that she's the killer,

46:37.751 --> 46:39.231
because having a cop dad
is a great cover.

46:39.405 --> 46:41.711
Do you not remember
how these movies work, Tara?

46:42.495 --> 46:44.149
Is she always like this?

46:44.323 --> 46:46.368
And finally... Anika.

46:48.675 --> 46:50.590
Never trust the love interest.

46:53.419 --> 46:57.553
Okay! So, we have our rules
and we have our suspects.

46:57.727 --> 46:59.338
But wait.
What about you guys?

46:59.512 --> 47:02.732
I mean, I think it's pretty safe
to rule out the four of us

47:02.907 --> 47:04.996
who went through this last year
in Woodsboro.

47:05.170 --> 47:07.215
- Agreed.
- Um, not agreed.

47:07.389 --> 47:09.609
What if the trauma
you all went through

47:09.783 --> 47:12.525
caused one
or more of you to snap?

47:12.699 --> 47:16.398
Yeah, or the fame you got
from the killings
made you thirsty for more.

47:16.572 --> 47:18.009
I mean, let's be honest here,

47:18.183 --> 47:20.446
some of the theories online
about Sam are--

47:20.620 --> 47:22.056
Don't you fucking dare.

47:22.230 --> 47:24.885
Okay, she's right, though.

47:25.059 --> 47:26.278
I mean, face facts--

47:26.452 --> 47:28.323
if we're all suspects,
you're all suspects.

47:37.332 --> 47:41.684
Remember Samantha Carpenter's
- alibi, the therapist?
- Mm-hmm.

47:41.859 --> 47:44.905
He was stabbed
- to death. Through the nose.
- Mmm.

47:45.079 --> 47:47.299
Through the nose.
How messed up is that?

47:47.473 --> 47:49.518
It's pretty messed up.

47:49.692 --> 47:52.347
He turned her in
for making threatening remarks,

47:52.521 --> 47:53.827
ended up dead.

47:54.001 --> 47:56.090
And guess which patient's
notes were stolen?

47:57.657 --> 48:00.878
So Sam kills her own alibi and
steals her own session notes?

48:01.052 --> 48:02.096
Maybe.

48:03.315 --> 48:04.707
Another mask
was found at the scene.

48:05.665 --> 48:07.362
It's a DNA match
for Roman Bridger.

48:07.536 --> 48:10.322
The Ghostface
who was directing <i>Stab 3.</i>

48:11.758 --> 48:14.892
It's like he's leaving us
real-life franchise Easter eggs.

48:15.066 --> 48:18.634
Like dropping
the killers' masks in reverse.

48:18.808 --> 48:21.333
Almost like he's counting down
to something.

48:22.551 --> 48:24.031
What happens
when he gets to one?

48:29.080 --> 48:32.039
So we've had nine
Ghostface killers so far.

48:32.213 --> 48:33.606
Nine. I thought in the movies--

48:33.780 --> 48:36.043
Forget about the movies.
The movies don't matter.

48:36.217 --> 48:39.655
Look. Last year was
Amber Freeman and Richie Kirsch,

48:39.829 --> 48:41.614
whose masks we found
at the first crime scene

48:41.788 --> 48:44.008
along with the bodies
of two film students

48:44.182 --> 48:46.836
who killed their professor
earlier that same night.

48:47.011 --> 48:49.883
Then it was Jill Roberts
and Charlie Walker--

48:50.057 --> 48:51.319
theirs at the bodega.

48:51.493 --> 48:53.843
Roman Bridger was the only
single Ghostface.

48:54.018 --> 48:55.236
Kudos to him for ambition.

48:55.410 --> 48:57.717
His mask
was found at the shrink's.

48:57.891 --> 49:01.373
Which leaves Mickey Altieri,
Nancy Loomis, Stu Macher...

49:01.547 --> 49:03.853
...and Billy Loomis. Number one.

49:04.028 --> 49:05.943
And the father
of our chief suspect.

49:07.509 --> 49:10.686
Well, whoever's doing this
is leading us back to Sam.

49:14.603 --> 49:15.996
I will check in later.

49:16.170 --> 49:18.172
And tell your daughter
to stay sharp.

49:18.346 --> 49:21.393
Proximity to the Carpenters
is proximity to Ghostface.

49:31.229 --> 49:34.014
Hey, Jack? Would you call
the Atlanta field office?

49:35.015 --> 49:36.974
Dig up what you can
on Agent Reed.

49:43.981 --> 49:45.460
I think you should
get out of the city.

49:45.634 --> 49:48.289
You know, considering
what happened to you
last time.

49:48.463 --> 49:53.077
I-- I wouldn't blame you
if... you wanted to go.

49:55.601 --> 49:58.169
That's very thoughtful of you,
but, um,

49:59.561 --> 50:01.085
I don't think
I'm going anywhere.

50:02.477 --> 50:04.479
Will you two
just make out already?

50:04.653 --> 50:07.004
That is so inappropriate,
- dude.
- Oh, whatever.

50:07.178 --> 50:08.701
Get it over with!

50:08.875 --> 50:09.789
Here you go.

50:09.963 --> 50:11.530
Sam?[Sam] Yep?

50:11.704 --> 50:13.662
We do not
have to stay here.

50:13.836 --> 50:16.622
Well, too bad. I insist.
Safety in numbers.

50:16.796 --> 50:18.145
This'll be so fun.

50:18.319 --> 50:19.973
A little slumber party
with the Core Four!

50:20.147 --> 50:21.496
- "Core Four"?
- Yeah.

50:21.670 --> 50:23.324
- Did you give us a nickname?
- I sure did.

50:23.498 --> 50:24.760
We've been through
a lot together,

50:24.934 --> 50:26.501
and it's a pretty cool nickname.

50:26.675 --> 50:28.329
- That's debatable.
- It's extremely debatable.

50:28.503 --> 50:30.244
You can't just give yourself
a nickname, dingus.

50:30.418 --> 50:32.638
Of course I can, dingus,
because I just did.

50:32.812 --> 50:34.770
- Core Four, up top!
- No.

50:34.944 --> 50:36.207
- Down low.
- Get that away from me.

50:36.381 --> 50:38.513
Please,
- for the love of God.
- Don't do it.

50:38.687 --> 50:41.212
I would like a little more
respect and support

50:41.386 --> 50:43.605
from my fellow members
of the Core Four.

50:44.389 --> 50:46.304
Guys. What the hell?

50:46.478 --> 50:49.611
<i>We're hearing from sources
inside the homicide division</i>

50:49.785 --> 50:53.659
<i>that the prime suspect is none
other than Samantha Carpenter,</i>

50:53.833 --> 50:57.228
<i>one of the survivors of
the Woodsboro killings in 2022,</i>

50:57.402 --> 51:00.753
<i>seen here attacking a woman
on the street last night.</i>

51:00.927 --> 51:02.755
<i>is wrong with you?</i>

51:02.929 --> 51:05.105
<i>You got a problem with me?
Knock it off!</i>

51:05.279 --> 51:07.281
<i>Stay away from her.
She knows what she did.</i>

51:07.455 --> 51:09.544
<i>In the wake
of the Woodsboro tragedy
last year,</i>

51:09.718 --> 51:11.372
<i>rumors sprouted online</i>

51:11.546 --> 51:14.984
<i>that Carpenter was actually
responsible for the killings,</i>

51:15.159 --> 51:17.813
<i>blaming the crimes
on her boyfriend, Richie Kirsch</i>

51:17.987 --> 51:19.815
<i>and teen Amber Free--</i>

51:42.273 --> 51:45.276
I know you're not a fan
of the way
that I've been handling things,

51:45.450 --> 51:47.582
and that I've been giving you
a really hard time.

51:47.756 --> 51:48.931
But I can say

51:50.324 --> 51:52.935
that none of us can relate
to what you are experiencing.

51:56.591 --> 51:59.333
And I'm really, really sorry
that you have to do that alone.

52:03.903 --> 52:05.078
It's not your fault.

52:06.819 --> 52:09.691
And I know I shouldn't care
what people think.

52:11.867 --> 52:14.696
It just sucks
being this hated.

52:17.264 --> 52:20.224
Hey. Hey. Just a reminder,

52:20.398 --> 52:23.488
not a single person
in this room hates you.

52:23.662 --> 52:27.535
Okay?
We have all been through
some fucked-up stuff,

52:27.709 --> 52:30.277
and we are
coping with it differently.

52:30.451 --> 52:32.323
But, I mean,
we moved here together

52:32.497 --> 52:34.368
for one
very specific reason.

52:37.241 --> 52:38.285
We are a team.

52:42.420 --> 52:43.464
We are

52:43.638 --> 52:45.249
the Core Fucking Four.

52:45.423 --> 52:47.251
- Thank you very much.
- Ah, I hate myself.

52:47.425 --> 52:49.557
You said it.
That is what I'm talking about.

52:49.731 --> 52:51.211
It's the Core Four.

52:51.385 --> 52:53.300
Say it.[Tara] I'm not gonna say it.

52:53.474 --> 52:54.954
I mean, yes,
we're a team, but...

52:55.128 --> 52:56.738
It's got a nice ring to it.

52:56.912 --> 52:59.872
I've been sleeping with Cute Boy
from across the hall.

53:03.441 --> 53:05.138
- Boom!
- I fucking knew it!

53:05.312 --> 53:07.967
- I knew it, I knew it.
- You called it.

53:08.141 --> 53:10.056
I knew it from the day
you had that hickey.

53:11.927 --> 53:14.191
<i>Sales
of the Ghostface Halloween mask</i>

53:14.365 --> 53:19.021
<i>across the Tri-State area
in the last 24 hours
have gone through the roof!</i>

53:19.196 --> 53:20.588
<i>I've got my mask.</i>

53:20.762 --> 53:22.024
<i>What about you, Jay?</i>[Jay] <i>You know it.</i>

53:22.199 --> 53:24.592
<i>It's gonna be
one spooky Halloween.</i>

53:24.766 --> 53:26.594
<i>I'll say. Now, let's get over to Guy
for a look at our weather.</i>

53:28.161 --> 53:31.599
I know she's my roommate,
but you're, like, the police.

53:33.035 --> 53:34.385
Yo.

53:35.734 --> 53:37.257
[Quinn] No, I know.

53:37.431 --> 53:38.650
Hey!

53:39.564 --> 53:40.869
Fuck.

53:41.043 --> 53:42.828
Hey, yeah.
Wassup, bitch?

53:43.002 --> 53:45.091
I see you, motherfucker.

53:46.701 --> 53:48.442
Sam! Samantha!

53:48.616 --> 53:50.705
I feel like we should high five
or something.

53:50.879 --> 53:52.577
The Core Four High Five--
may we, please?

53:52.751 --> 53:54.840
Don't call it that,
but we'll do the high five.

53:55.014 --> 53:56.450
Come on.

53:56.624 --> 53:59.279
Sam! Samantha!

53:59.453 --> 54:01.150
Sam, what the fuck?

54:01.325 --> 54:03.762
She's really
freaked out and paranoid.

54:03.936 --> 54:06.155
Babe, you gonna join me?[Quinn] Hang on.

54:06.330 --> 54:08.332
No. And don't use
my good face wash.

54:08.506 --> 54:10.464
It's pH-balanced for women.

54:11.509 --> 54:12.858
Pick up your phone, baby.

54:16.905 --> 54:18.559
Is that him?

54:18.733 --> 54:21.910
- No, Tara. Not right now.
- Hey, what are your intentions?

54:22.084 --> 54:23.869
[Chad] That's right.

54:24.043 --> 54:26.350
It's fine. I'll call him back.

54:26.524 --> 54:28.003
Poor guy.[Chad] Okay.

54:30.832 --> 54:33.270
Quinn and her gentleman caller
are back at it again.

54:33.444 --> 54:35.315
She's getting it,
too? Okay.

54:52.245 --> 54:53.855
Help! Stop!

54:55.553 --> 54:56.815
Tara, wait, wait!

55:06.433 --> 55:07.434
Run.

55:08.566 --> 55:10.394
Oh, shit!

55:13.005 --> 55:14.267
Guys, come on!

55:15.268 --> 55:17.096
Oh, fuck.

55:18.010 --> 55:19.533
[Anika] Mindy!

55:19.707 --> 55:21.274
Stay the fuck back!

55:45.167 --> 55:46.212
Hey!

55:50.782 --> 55:52.131
Wait, wait, Chad!

55:52.305 --> 55:53.785
- They're still up there.
- Shit!

56:01.445 --> 56:02.446
Fuck.

56:04.709 --> 56:06.928
- Sam!
- Do you have the keys?

56:07.102 --> 56:08.539
No, I left them inside!

56:17.243 --> 56:19.419
Mindy, bathroom door. Hurry!

56:21.987 --> 56:23.771
Oh, fuck! That guy's dead.

56:44.705 --> 56:46.054
Oh, shit.

56:47.012 --> 56:48.361
Oh, fuck.

56:50.015 --> 56:50.972
Hey!

56:54.715 --> 56:55.716
Hey!

56:57.805 --> 56:58.893
Shit.

57:02.331 --> 57:03.985
Don't worry,
I got you.

57:05.900 --> 57:07.946
- Are you fucking kidding me?
- You have a better idea?

57:08.729 --> 57:10.035
Fuck. No.

57:16.868 --> 57:19.000
You have to come
one at a time.

57:19.174 --> 57:21.394
- You two go first. Mindy!
- What? No.

57:21.568 --> 57:22.917
Someone needs
to hold the door.

57:23.091 --> 57:25.398
I'll send Anika next. Go!

57:26.443 --> 57:28.793
Sam, come on.
Eyes on me, baby.

57:28.967 --> 57:30.359
Keep your eyes on me.

57:31.796 --> 57:32.797
Oh, shit.

57:34.015 --> 57:36.496
Oh, my God.[Danny] I got you, baby.

57:39.456 --> 57:40.761
Baby, come on!

57:41.762 --> 57:43.372
It won't hold me.

57:43.547 --> 57:45.113
Okay.

57:45.287 --> 57:47.333
It ain't going anywhere.
It's gonna hold you, I promise.

57:47.507 --> 57:48.508
Danny.

57:52.338 --> 57:54.601
I got you.
You ain't going nowhere.
Let's go.

57:54.775 --> 57:58.692
- She's losing a lot of blood!
- Say something more positive!

57:58.866 --> 58:01.216
Eyes on me, Sam.
Come on, baby.

58:01.390 --> 58:04.611
[Danny] Come on. I got you.

58:04.785 --> 58:06.265
Come on, I got you.

58:10.443 --> 58:11.270
Okay.

58:11.444 --> 58:12.793
- Come on!
- Let's go!

58:12.967 --> 58:15.187
- Come on, Mindy!
- Let's go, we got to move!

58:15.361 --> 58:16.797
Anika, come on!

58:18.582 --> 58:20.975
Anika![Danny] Go! Come on!

58:21.149 --> 58:23.195
You have to go first.[Anika whimpering] I can't.

58:24.152 --> 58:25.502
You have to go.

58:25.676 --> 58:28.287
Mindy, no! I'll be
right behind you, I promise.

58:32.726 --> 58:34.728
Mindy, come on.
You got to get over here!

58:34.902 --> 58:36.077
Let's go!

58:37.209 --> 58:39.690
We got you.[Sam] That's it. Mindy.

58:39.864 --> 58:41.822
Slow and steady.[Sam] We got you.

58:42.954 --> 58:44.912
Oh, God.

58:45.086 --> 58:48.829
Baby, you can't stop.[Sam] Get over here right now!

58:49.003 --> 58:51.484
Anika's coming right behind you.

58:55.793 --> 58:58.404
Anika, come on![Danny] Go!

58:58.578 --> 59:00.798
You can do it![Mindy] Come on, Anika!

59:00.972 --> 59:04.236
Oh, God!
I can't do it, I can't do it.

59:05.759 --> 59:07.805
Don't look down![Mindy] Look at me!

59:07.979 --> 59:11.025
You can do it!
You're doing good.

59:17.554 --> 59:18.816
What?

59:18.990 --> 59:20.600
Anika, you have to move
right now!

59:23.211 --> 59:24.386
No, God! Please, no!

59:24.561 --> 59:25.692
Anika, you got to move!

59:28.173 --> 59:29.174
No!

59:36.007 --> 59:37.574
You have to make it!

59:37.748 --> 59:39.314
Baby, I don't want to die!

59:39.488 --> 59:41.142
No, Anika.

59:45.146 --> 59:47.453
Anika, give me your hand.
I got you.

59:57.768 --> 59:59.857
No!

1:00:23.968 --> 1:00:26.057
So are you
pullin' anybody for interviews?

1:00:26.231 --> 1:00:27.841
How far along are you on that?

1:00:28.015 --> 1:00:29.321
Uh, just got two.

1:00:31.410 --> 1:00:32.541
Okay.

1:00:34.587 --> 1:00:36.415
Hey. You okay?

1:00:40.767 --> 1:00:42.464
This isn't your fault, Sam.

1:00:43.814 --> 1:00:44.815
But it is.

1:00:49.907 --> 1:00:51.691
Someone took our knives,

1:00:52.474 --> 1:00:54.128
so we couldn't fight back.

1:00:54.912 --> 1:00:56.653
I don't know
who I can trust.

1:00:59.046 --> 1:01:02.354
Then don't trust anyone.
Not your friends. Not me.

1:01:03.485 --> 1:01:04.965
Not anyone.

1:01:05.139 --> 1:01:07.272
I have
a few more questions for you.

1:01:09.187 --> 1:01:10.405
Just this way, Danny.

1:01:17.717 --> 1:01:18.718
Chad.

1:01:21.895 --> 1:01:23.462
- Where were you?
- What? When?

1:01:23.636 --> 1:01:24.550
- Last night!
- What?

1:01:24.724 --> 1:01:25.943
I had Econ.
You know this.

1:01:26.117 --> 1:01:27.161
Bullshit, man!
You disappear,

1:01:27.335 --> 1:01:28.859
and my sister
almost gets killed!

1:01:29.033 --> 1:01:30.904
Dude, I was in a study hall
with a hundred other people.

1:01:31.078 --> 1:01:32.689
You can ask any of them.

1:01:33.690 --> 1:01:34.691
Fuck, man.

1:01:36.475 --> 1:01:37.563
Oh, my God.

1:01:38.607 --> 1:01:40.827
Who?[Chad] Anika and Quinn.

1:01:42.786 --> 1:01:44.875
Mindy, I'm so sorry.

1:01:45.049 --> 1:01:46.572
Step the fuck back.

1:01:48.400 --> 1:01:49.880
You're at the top of my list.

1:01:50.619 --> 1:01:51.882
I had Econ!

1:02:01.718 --> 1:02:03.154
Go right ahead, sir.

1:02:08.202 --> 1:02:09.943
I'm gonna be right back.

1:02:17.429 --> 1:02:18.691
I'm really sorry
about Quinn.

1:02:20.301 --> 1:02:21.694
Thank you.

1:02:24.436 --> 1:02:26.090
Both my kids are gone.

1:02:27.134 --> 1:02:29.049
My whole family...

1:02:29.223 --> 1:02:30.529
...is gone.

1:02:34.968 --> 1:02:36.709
They took me
off the case.

1:02:36.883 --> 1:02:39.190
But I'm not gonna stop
until I find him.

1:02:40.104 --> 1:02:41.627
You fuck with my family...

1:02:43.063 --> 1:02:44.064
you die.

1:02:45.413 --> 1:02:46.719
Agreed.

1:02:46.893 --> 1:02:49.635
Hey, are you okay?
I came as soon as I heard.

1:02:49.809 --> 1:02:51.115
Gale, I swear to God...

1:02:51.289 --> 1:02:54.074
Truce, okay?
I'm here for whatever you need.

1:02:54.248 --> 1:02:55.336
Okay. Nice try.

1:02:55.510 --> 1:02:56.990
Really, I am.

1:02:58.252 --> 1:03:00.037
Okay, fine.
Off the record, okay?

1:03:03.910 --> 1:03:05.738
Okay. Thank you.

1:03:09.960 --> 1:03:11.962
I'm sorry I punched you.

1:03:12.658 --> 1:03:13.920
No, you're not.

1:03:14.094 --> 1:03:15.182
I'm not.

1:03:17.315 --> 1:03:19.273
You're the cop, right?

1:03:19.447 --> 1:03:21.319
I did some digging
on your first two victims

1:03:21.493 --> 1:03:22.624
and I found something.

1:03:22.799 --> 1:03:25.018
I know where the masks
are coming from.

1:03:25.192 --> 1:03:26.454
Show me.

1:03:26.628 --> 1:03:27.542
Ladies.

1:03:28.587 --> 1:03:29.806
Kirby?

1:03:30.589 --> 1:03:31.677
Gale.

1:03:31.851 --> 1:03:33.897
She's with the FBI.She's a child.

1:03:34.071 --> 1:03:36.116
When did they start
letting children into the FBI?

1:03:36.290 --> 1:03:39.119
- I'm 30.
- Well, you look like a zygote.

1:03:39.293 --> 1:03:40.599
I have a gun, Gale.

1:03:40.773 --> 1:03:43.297
Okay, fine. You're gonna
want to see this, too.

1:03:45.734 --> 1:03:48.650
Jason and Greg
were little Atlanta rich boys.

1:03:48.825 --> 1:03:51.392
Apparently, they used
fake names to rent this place.

1:03:51.566 --> 1:03:53.090
How did you find it?

1:03:53.264 --> 1:03:56.006
It's called
"investigative journalism"
for a reason.

1:03:56.180 --> 1:03:59.836
How didn't you find it?
Weren't you tracking them?

1:04:00.010 --> 1:04:02.708
I went through
their financial records
dozens of times.

1:04:02.882 --> 1:04:05.580
This was not in any of them.
Doesn't make sense.

1:04:05.754 --> 1:04:07.234
Don't worry.

1:04:07.408 --> 1:04:09.323
I'm just really good at my job.
You'll get there.

1:04:22.293 --> 1:04:25.949
What is this place?
What's with all the security?

1:04:29.561 --> 1:04:30.910
It's a movie theater.

1:04:31.084 --> 1:04:32.607
It's not just a theater.

1:04:33.434 --> 1:04:34.827
It's a shrine.

1:04:51.800 --> 1:04:52.845
Whoa.

1:05:08.339 --> 1:05:11.211
They've got
the whole goddamn franchise.

1:05:26.270 --> 1:05:27.793
- Chad?
- Mmm?

1:05:28.446 --> 1:05:29.838
This was Uncle Randy's.

1:05:31.014 --> 1:05:32.406
They've got everything.

1:05:35.757 --> 1:05:37.716
Is that--The knife I was stabbed with.

1:05:37.890 --> 1:05:40.023
You all have been through
so much.

1:05:41.502 --> 1:05:43.635
Who drew all these?

1:05:57.605 --> 1:05:58.737
Dewey.

1:05:58.911 --> 1:06:00.957
Hey, how'd they get
all this stuff?

1:06:02.175 --> 1:06:03.524
Isn't this evidence?

1:06:03.698 --> 1:06:05.439
Well, cops like money,

1:06:05.613 --> 1:06:08.834
and evidence can get lost
pretty easily.

1:06:10.618 --> 1:06:12.794
Present company excluded,
of course.

1:06:15.145 --> 1:06:18.365
Um, why am I here exactly?
My alibi checks out.

1:06:18.539 --> 1:06:21.151
So I can keep an eye on you, roomie.

1:06:22.282 --> 1:06:23.544
The killer must have
found this place

1:06:23.718 --> 1:06:25.459
before he murdered Jason
and Greg.

1:06:25.633 --> 1:06:28.593
And then he took the masks
off the mannequins.

1:06:28.767 --> 1:06:31.900
All nine, from Stu and Billy
to Amber and Richie.

1:06:57.622 --> 1:07:00.712
Hot damn!
How fucking cool is this place?

1:07:00.886 --> 1:07:02.105
Fuck, no.

1:07:02.279 --> 1:07:03.367
Fuck, yes.

1:07:03.541 --> 1:07:05.325
Come on, Sam,
you got to be excited

1:07:05.499 --> 1:07:08.111
to get our murder on again. Together.

1:07:08.285 --> 1:07:11.244
Billy and Sam.
Team Loomis.

1:07:11.418 --> 1:07:14.682
Get ready to slice up
more motherfuckers.

1:07:25.258 --> 1:07:26.781
What are you doing?

1:07:31.264 --> 1:07:32.657
I don't know.

1:07:37.140 --> 1:07:38.793
So,

1:07:38.967 --> 1:07:41.187
somebody killed
these chucklefucks

1:07:42.058 --> 1:07:43.537
and took over?

1:07:43.711 --> 1:07:46.584
Someone who believes that Sam
masterminded Woodsboro.

1:07:46.758 --> 1:07:48.194
If this were
a normal <i>Stab</i> movie,

1:07:48.368 --> 1:07:50.066
this would be the killer's lair.

1:07:50.240 --> 1:07:52.764
Which means this isn't
a normal <i>Stab</i> movie.

1:08:08.823 --> 1:08:11.435
The TV that killed Stu Macher.

1:08:11.609 --> 1:08:13.263
If you believe he's dead.

1:08:15.352 --> 1:08:17.223
I hear
you're a horror fan.

1:08:18.006 --> 1:08:19.486
- It's been said.
- Mmm.

1:08:19.660 --> 1:08:20.792
Mmm.

1:08:20.966 --> 1:08:22.750
Best <i>Nightmare
on Elm Street?</i>

1:08:22.924 --> 1:08:24.361
The original.

1:08:24.535 --> 1:08:26.232
Best <i>Friday the 13th?</i>

1:08:26.406 --> 1:08:27.668
Part II.The Final Chapter.

1:08:29.409 --> 1:08:30.671
Had a crush
on Corey Feldman.

1:08:30.845 --> 1:08:32.456
Okay. Respect.

1:08:33.848 --> 1:08:34.762
<i>Psycho II</i> is...

1:08:34.936 --> 1:08:36.024
...underrated.

1:08:37.287 --> 1:08:40.072
<i>Candyman.</i>
The original or requel?

1:08:40.246 --> 1:08:41.160
Both.

1:08:42.683 --> 1:08:44.729
Okay. Okay.

1:08:44.903 --> 1:08:46.513
Game recognize game.

1:08:47.862 --> 1:08:49.168
Hmm.

1:08:53.694 --> 1:08:55.131
You okay?

1:08:58.003 --> 1:09:00.266
Sam, when do I get
to be a normal person again?

1:09:03.269 --> 1:09:04.444
I don't know.

1:09:04.618 --> 1:09:06.533
I don't want
to be a part of this.

1:09:07.839 --> 1:09:09.667
I don't want to be a part
of some stupid legacy

1:09:09.841 --> 1:09:11.408
because I'm--Because of me.

1:09:14.106 --> 1:09:16.195
I'm sorry.

1:09:16.369 --> 1:09:17.588
Just drop it, Sam.

1:09:19.459 --> 1:09:20.460
Tara.

1:09:21.374 --> 1:09:22.332
I got her.

1:09:27.337 --> 1:09:28.729
That seemed intense.

1:09:30.166 --> 1:09:32.777
Ever since I came back
into her life, I've just...

1:09:35.693 --> 1:09:37.129
made a mess of it.

1:09:37.651 --> 1:09:38.696
Hey.

1:09:38.870 --> 1:09:40.611
Where's your mother
in all this?

1:09:40.785 --> 1:09:44.136
She cut me off
when I told Tara
about Billy.

1:09:45.006 --> 1:09:46.094
Then Tara cut her off

1:09:46.269 --> 1:09:48.706
because she wouldn't
talk to me,

1:09:48.880 --> 1:09:51.317
so now neither of us
have a mother.

1:09:51.491 --> 1:09:53.885
I'm sorry to say this,
but fuck her.

1:09:54.755 --> 1:09:56.192
My parents sucked, too.

1:09:58.019 --> 1:10:00.239
But you can still
make your own family.

1:10:00.413 --> 1:10:02.720
Even if it's just
with one person.

1:10:06.898 --> 1:10:09.292
And if you lose
that one person?

1:10:11.294 --> 1:10:12.860
You just-- You keep going.

1:10:14.210 --> 1:10:15.515
And maybe
you find another loner,

1:10:15.689 --> 1:10:17.561
and you look after each other.

1:10:26.004 --> 1:10:28.049
How'd you get past
what happened to you?

1:10:33.446 --> 1:10:35.361
I almost died
after I was stabbed.

1:10:37.189 --> 1:10:38.625
Technically, I did die.

1:10:38.799 --> 1:10:40.279
For four minutes.

1:10:43.413 --> 1:10:44.588
When I recovered...

1:10:45.806 --> 1:10:47.678
I got mad.

1:10:47.852 --> 1:10:51.508
I didn't want
to spend the rest of my life
being afraid of monsters.

1:10:53.292 --> 1:10:55.773
I wanted the monsters
to be afraid of me.

1:10:57.035 --> 1:10:58.341
I like that.

1:10:58.515 --> 1:11:00.647
[Bailey] Sorry to interrupt.

1:11:01.561 --> 1:11:02.780
Think I might have an idea

1:11:02.954 --> 1:11:04.216
about how to turn the tables
on this creep.

1:11:04.390 --> 1:11:06.218
Yeah. We're in.

1:11:06.392 --> 1:11:08.481
Sorry, Gale.
No press allowed.

1:11:08.655 --> 1:11:10.875
Police business.
I'm good at my job, too.

1:11:17.795 --> 1:11:19.405
You should have stayed
with the others.

1:11:19.579 --> 1:11:21.189
That's not gonna happen.

1:11:21.364 --> 1:11:24.410
There's no point in both of us
putting ourselves at risk.

1:11:24.584 --> 1:11:27.283
I'm not.
I'm your backup.

1:11:31.722 --> 1:11:33.680
So we're really doing
the phone tracing thing

1:11:33.854 --> 1:11:35.552
that never works
in the movies.

1:11:35.726 --> 1:11:37.554
It'll be all, "Keep him talking,
Sam. Two more minutes,

1:11:37.728 --> 1:11:39.251
I've almost got him."

1:11:39.425 --> 1:11:41.427
And then he hangs up just
before we can get a lock.

1:11:41.601 --> 1:11:45.083
I can trace a call
in under 15 seconds.

1:11:47.390 --> 1:11:50.393
Well, you've got them
out there as bait.

1:11:50.567 --> 1:11:52.395
Because the killer usually calls
from somewhere nearby.

1:11:52.569 --> 1:11:54.701
And you think they're safe
because it's broad daylight

1:11:54.875 --> 1:11:56.050
in a public place?

1:11:56.224 --> 1:11:58.357
Look, I am here, okay?
And so is Bailey.

1:11:58.531 --> 1:12:01.055
This is exactly
how our Uncle Randy died.

